results.name: a(1)=1, a(2) = 2; thereafter a(n) = the smallest positive integer which does not occur earlier in the sequence and which is coprime to a(n-2).
comment: Permutation of the positive natural numbers with inverse A225047: a(A225047(n)) = A225047(a(n)) = n. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Apr 25 2013
I confirm that this is a permutation. - _N. J. A. Sloane_, Mar 28 2015

Index entries for sequences that are permutations of the natural numbers
mathematica: Nest[Append[#, Block[{k = 3}, While[Nand[FreeQ[#, k], GCD[#[[-2]], k] == 1], k++]; k]] &, {1, 2}, 70] (* _Michael De Vlieger_, Dec 26 2019 *)
program: f x y zs = g zs where
g (u:us) = if gcd x u == 1 then h $ delete u zs else g us where
h (v:vs) = if gcd y v == 1 then u : v : f u v (zs \\ [u,v]) else h vs
